<title>A man respects his wife&apos;s mother</title>
<summary>A man respects his mother-in-law&apos;s name and does not speak it. His mother-in-law addresses him as &apos;son-in-law&apos;. When his mother-in-law is silent he is silent. He addresses his wife&apos;s father as his <i>≠khumm</i>.</summary><comments>1) p.9834v: an explanation of the terms ≠khumm and |ui sau, which are used for addressing the father- or son-in-law and the mother- and daughter-in-law, 2) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-10</comments><date>27 May 1881 </date><storypages>9832-9835</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><keyword><kw>address</kw><subkw>a man respects his wife&apos;s mother</subkw></keyword>
